    "name": "Leah Marquez",
    "subtitle": "Representative from the Healthy Child Screening program",
    "quote": "The Toronto College of Dental Hygiene and Auxiliaries has been collaborating with The Four Villages Community Health Centre since 2009. Dental hygiene students, accompanied and supervised by a clinical instructor, provide dental screening and education for children ages 2 to 6 years and their parents/caregivers. The dental screening is a key component of the Healthy Child Screening, which includes assessments from nurses, dietitians, speech and language pathologists, social workers, settlement workers, optometrists, and hearing screeners from a variety of community agencies. Many families attending the screening are newcomers, have little knowledge of English, low-income, and may have limited access to health services including dental care. Students see first-hand the value of collaborating with other health professionals to improve both individual and community health. The Healthy Child Screening program enables students to give back to the community while benefiting the families in attendance. Students of The Toronto College of Dental Hygiene and Auxiliaries are professional, reliable, punctual, approachable, and enthusiastic in dealing with staff and families alike.",
