    "quote": "Good afternoon fellow graduates, friends, family, Dean of students, Dr. Pulec, Business director, Ms. Lidia DiNicolo, program coordinator, Mrs. Lila Mc Indoe and the faculty of TCDHA. It is a great honor to be here. These past 18 months have flown by and it is hard to believe that before we know it we will be out in the working environment. Before I begin, I would like to take a moment to thank all of you sitting here today for giving me this opportunity to speak in front of you on this special occasion. When I first came to this school I was unsure I would even handle the workload let alone be standing here today as your valedictorian and I am extremely proud to represent the graduating class of 2014. I would also like to thank the faculty at TCDHA for giving us each a piece of something to take with us into the dental hygiene field. As a class, we have been through more than we could have imagined in these past 18 months. Some more difficult to face than others. Especially those of us with children who know it's not easy to do our homework when our kids are trying to color in our textbooks. Or study for a test when they are crying. At first I felt guilty not spending enough time with my son because of school, but I kept telling myself that sacrifice is only temporary, but I will be a college graduate forever. As I stand up here today and all my hard work has paid off, I know my son and family are so proud of me. As I am sure all of you are as proud of all your graduates sitting here today. Yet we are sitting here for a reason. We are here because of our goals and dreams that have pushed us to accomplish all things. Look into the stands and to others around you. Every single person sitting here today sees something in you and believes that you will do great things in your lives. It doesn't matter what your plans are, or what you consider to be \"great things.\" Just remember that you can. You can try, you can fail, and you can try again. Graduation is a new start with new opportunities and no matter what path you choose to follow as you progress into your future, you will be the best that you can be. Not only am I excited to see what lies ahead, I know that the people sitting here today and the people that support you feel the same way about you. Today we have the good feel factor that comes from knowing that we have done our best. We have achieved and qualified. We didn't do it alone of course. All along the way we had the wonderful support of our families and the encouragement and help of our faculty. Today, though, as mature and newly qualified adults, we recognize that without that backup we could not have succeeded. So today I know my fellow students would like to join me in saying how much we appreciate all those who have helped make this day possible. Finally, I would like to wish my fellow graduates health and happiness in the future and the satisfaction of knowing that whatever they do they will do it well. After all they are graduates of TCDHA and that is just another name for the college of excellence. Congratulations, Class of 2014. And thank you.",
